    "longBusinessSummary": "CII Bridges and Roads Investment Joint Stock Company, together with its subsidiaries, provides traffic toll collection services in Vietnam. It engages in the construction of railway and road projects, and civil engineering and public works, as well as the construction and installation of public lighting equipment systems, and the maintenance of public works. The company also invests in construction, exploitation, and trading of urban technical infrastructures under build-operate-transfer (B.O.T.). In addition, it engages in electrical system installation; manufacture and repair of electrical equipment; architectural activities and related technical consultancy services; wholesale of other installation materials and equipment in construction; manufacture of metal structures and other products of metal; installation of other building systems; retail sale of motor fuel in specialized stores; and provision of health promotion services. Further, the company is involved in coastal and sea, and inland waterway freight; exploitation, treatment, and supply of water; water supply and drainage system installation; and real estate businesses. The company was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam. CII Bridges and Roads Investment Joint Stock Company is a subsidiary of Ho Chi Minh City Technical Infrastructure Investment Joint Stock Company.",
